[normal]2
[normal].
[normal](c)[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]How much do natural processes absorb &amp; emit into atmosphere?
[normal]Over 90% of all 
[normal]CO
[normal]2  
[normal]flows both into and out of the atmosphere are natural. In historic time series, CO
[normal]2
[normal] rises in response to increasing temperatures. Temperature appears to drive 
[normal]CO
[normal]2 
[normal]levels. It is therefore quite possible that all man-made CO
[normal]2
[normal] can be absorbed, so that whether or not we produced any CO
[normal]2
[normal], that changes in atmospheric levels would occur naturally as a result of naturally changing temperature (as has occurred naturally many times).
[normal](d)[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]What is the net human contribution to rising CO
[normal]2
[normal]?
[normal]The IPCC assert that all the rise is human. Prof 
[normal]Murry
[normal] Salby
[normal]9
[normal] has shown this assertion is false and that at least in part the change must be natural. And at a local level it is known naturally CO
[normal]2
[normal] levels increase in warmer period in S. America due to ENSO.
[normal] 3.[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]What will be the human contribution to CO[bold]2[bold] in atmosphere?[bold](a)[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
